          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Water in a cylindrical acrylic container",
                " (20.0 cm diameter, 26.5 cm length), with thickness of",
                "1.0 cm at ends and 0.5 cm at barrel walls."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN",
                "CSICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " LaBr3(Ce) scintillator (4.5 cm diameter,",
                "4.5 cm length) with Hamamatsu H6410 photomultiplier",
                "tube (PMT) reads gamma-rays from neutron-oxygen",
                "reactions. Positioned 20.5 cm from acrylic vessel,",
                "reducing neutron background. Acceptance angle is",
                "0.038 sr.",
                "For neutron flux measurement the acrylic container",
                "replaced with BC-501A organic liquid scintillator",
                " (5\" diameter, 8\" length) coupled with Hamamatsu",
                "H6527 PMT. Neutron scattering background measured with",
                "OKEN CsI(Tl) crystal (3.5 X 3.5 X 3.5 cm3) and",
                "H6410 PMT."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " High-purity germanium detector",
                " (ORTEC GEM 20180-P) used for precise gamma-ray",
                "detection. The detector consists of a cylindrical",
                "crystal (55 mm diameter, 46 mm length) with",
                "9.2 mm diameter hole, 33.4 mm depth."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The neutrons in the peak region (72 to 82 MeV) used for",
                "the measurement."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PSD",
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                " -The pulse-shape discrimination technique employed to",
                " distinguish between neutron-like and gamma-ray-like",
                " events",
                " - The kinetic energy of neutron-like events was",
                "derived from their Time-of-Flight within the",
                " scintillator.",
                " - The SCINFUL-QMD simulation is employed to calculate",
                "and correct for the detector's efficiency, ensuring",
                "accurate measurements of neutron flux.",
                " -Convert the detected neutron events into neutron flux",
                "accounting for both the detector efficiency and the",
                "cross-sectional area of the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The correction factor, which converts the flux measured",
                "by the BC-501A detector to the flux in the gamma-ray",
                "measurement with water is 1.09.",
                "Neutron flux 1.87 X 10**10 /Sr/uC, post-correction."
              ]
            }
          ],
